{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "7d75f26a-42cd-49fb-99ba-95f74f8f84e9",
    "name": "Diplomayn API",
    "description": "Complete collection for the dip Express backend.\n\n**Variables**\n- `baseUrl` — e.g. `http://localhost:5050` (no trailing slash).\n- `token` — paste `accessToken` from Register or Login into this variable for protected routes.\n- `refreshToken` — paste from Register/Login for the Refresh request body field mapping.\n- `userId` — target user id for `GET/PATCH /api/users/:id`.\n- `conversationId` — id from chat list or create response.\n\n**Notes**\n- Register requires `teacher_ids` (array of existing user ids with role `TICHER`).\n- Refresh body field is **`refresh_token`** (snake_case); the collection variable **`refreshToken`** is referenced as `{\"refresh_token\":\"{{refreshToken}}\"}`.\n- Admin routes need a user with `role` **ADMIN**.\n- `POST .../messages/stream` returns **SSE** (`text/event-stream`); Postman may buffer or behave differently than curl/browser.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5050"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "refreshToken",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "userId",
      "value": "1"
    },
    {
      "key": "conversationId",
      "value": "1"
    }
  ],
